meta.description: The Club SEA at Seattle-Tacoma International Airport (SEA), Concourse A. Learn more about the lounge: amenities, photos, review, opening hours, location.

lounge.name: The Club SEA
lounge.description: Immerse yourself in a quiet, welcoming oasis before your departure. Whatever your needs, this exclusive space has loads to offer. Enjoy a cocktail, attend to business matters, or take advantage of the peaceful atmosphere. Curl up with a good book or fall into a light slumber. Enjoy spectacular views while indulging in the complimentary bar service. Conveniently located in Concourse A, less than 5 minutes away from Concourse B.

general: Children under 2 years old are admitted free with an adult.
The lounge is currently undergoing refurbishment works until further notice. The lounge will remain open and disruption kept to a minimum.
regulatory: Access is only permitted 3 hours prior to scheduled flight departure.

reviews.content: Solid lounge with a decent amount of space. Monday night was very quiet. More private rooms in the back. Food was wraps and soup and salad bar. Worth a stop.
One of the better The Club lounges I’ve been to. Big enough, friendly service, the same food selection as the other Club lounges (which is pretty good).  They could stand to clean behind furniture.
Almost no food as of 11 AM. Only alcoholic, Coke, Sprite and some other juice as I saw. Hmm.
Spacious lounge, not too crowded when we were there on a Thursday morning until Noon. Super friendly staff, nice cocktails, decent food. A long way down the A Terminal...
Another dreadful American lounge with dreadful decor, terrible food and questionable hygiene. Drinks passable. Seating is uncomfortable and terribly cramped. Little to no charging outlets available.
Not allowing Priority Pass between 11a-1p. Very crowded, women at checkin seem overwhelmed and aren’t too friendly.
At least I was able to get in. It is located across from A11, which contrary to the blurb, is not so close to Concourse B. Food was OK.
Miserable food options. The small bar is the only reason to stop by.
This is a quiet little lounge for a bit of rest. Enough personal sofas around and a good view of the planes. Their cold food options are  reasonable.
Prepared food was very bland. Anything you make yourself was good. Bar was good, drinks were good. Service was great, always walking around cleaning.
Aging and somewhat depressing. Dodgy bathrooms, stained chairs, minimal food. This lounge doesn’t really serve a purpose.
OK lounge. Could use more power outlets. Only basic chairs, no place to stretch out. Wish it wasn’t so far from the other terminals.
This is a brutal lounge. Bad facilities. Packed all the time. Very low quality. Not worth it.
Breakfast-scones, pastries, yogurt parfaits, fruits, oatmeal, cheese omelettes, cereal, snacks, bar, coffee and tea. Lots of space in early am.  Frequent checks by servers of food and plates.
Soup, salad, and sandwiches available. Not too bad, just really far away from concourse B, C, and D.
Nothing exciting, but a decent sized quiet space. Amex lounge was over capacity so I checked this one out. I wouldn’t detour all the way to concourse A for a visit but worth a stop if already there.

Been coming here for last couple of years and they seemed to have cut down on snacks and drinks selections last month or so. Maybe it's just temporary things but gone are the Perrier's and all snacks.
Very basic lounge.  Depending on the time of day, you are probably better off sitting at one of the nicer airport restaurants. Pathetic food choice, with just a couple of crackers.
Typical airport lounge, comfy avg food not elaborate. Basic bar. Out of way unless you happen to be at a nearby gate.
I was there 10:30a limited seating. Line to check in. Limited food options. Coffee machine is slow and limited. Bartender was nice but rest of staff were cold and preoccupied. Dirty dishes. No bowls.
Nice lounge. Big variety for lunch. Good drinks. Roomy. Sweet view. Big bathrooms. I have no complaints.
Small selection of snacks (pre-packaged and not). Fairly crowded on a Monday midday, but staff was friendly and efficient. Bar has large selection of beer, wine, and even a few cocktails.

Visited the lounge on a quiet Tuesday afternoon. Plenty of seating AND they were serving Tattinger Champagne. For me, this alone makes it worth a detour as it's the best champ in a PP lounge I've seen.
Chairs comfortable, but nothing fancy. They do not have plugs to charge devices throughout lounge, you will have to find a chair near one. Drinks are complimentary.
Comfortable and clean. Plenty of vegan-friendly snack options.
Used PP at 4pm on a Thursday after being tired away at ASA lounges. Lounge was quite empty. Food included soup, fresh veggies, cheeses, etc. Clean and modern.
Bunch of packed Oreos, mini carrots, Lays potato chips in a bag and a mediocre coffee machine. View to a highway bridge.
PP approved 1430. Mostly empty. Light drinks/snacks.
Maybe it's because I'm here at 8 am, but there is no service, dirty cups laying about, meh food selection. Some chairs need replacing badly, they're falling apart.
Fine place to rest. Easy charging stations by chairs. Good drink selection. This location is open till midnight.
Got in with Priority Pass-- disappointing. Super crowded, no snacks, trash everywhere.
Very nice, clean and well stocked.

Rejected from Alaska lounge as PP holder and was directed here. Nothing to complains about, very open. Yeah they have a cup'o'noodles fountain at the bar, but lots of meal'able snacks and cleanliness.
Cup o noodles in an airport lounge? Seriously?
Enjoyed the service at this location. Much larger space than the satellite location, although without a view. Staff friendlier than any lounge I've visited. Full service bar a plus.
Clean lounge but limited food selection.
Good views, good chowder. Decent bar. Poor food selection. Hours are very limited. No dedicated wifi.
Out of the way location in SEA but worth it. Spacious, not crowded like Alaska's Boardroom. Free bartender mixed drinks plus soups, chips and snacks. Clean, new and stylish.
They heated up my leftover half a sandwich and presented it to me on a plate, very nice. Great free snacks and really good soup. Nice atmosphere and people were friendly. Had a great time.
Not a bad limited. If you don't have much time, right place to pop into. If you have time and it's near your gate I recommend the American Express Lounge.
Good location for Delta flights departing at the end of the A concourse.  However, those passengers who are in Delta First to Shanghai and Tokyo would need to use the Delta lounge in the S Satellite.
Comparable to many international lounges in terms of food offerings. Including instant noodles and other snacks. Nice lounge to relax in!
Overall nice lounge with friendly staff. Chardonnay is good and the clam chowder is worth the stop.
Good packaged snacks and bottled drinks and open bar. I also think it is better than the Alaska Board Room although it is in a much worse location.
Smaller lounge, but more available seating than a typical Sky Club.
Nice new lounge, with good snacks & beverages available.
Clean and relatively large relative to the number of passengers that pass through, this is a nice cozy lounge to grab a drink or some snacks before your flight.
While small, it is out of the way and not busy at all in the afternoon while I was here. A cooler with drinks so you can help yourself was nice. But typical limited snacks but enough to get by.

location.terminalDirections: Located after security, between Concourses B and C.
The new lounge is located on the mezzanine level in the Central Terminal. It is accessible by taking the elevator or staircase located in the food court in the Central Terminal.

otherLounges.name: Delta Air Lines Delta Sky Club

location.terminalDirections: Located at the juncture of Concourses A and B, near Gate A1.
After the Central Security Checkpoint, turn right and proceed to Concourse C, on the Mezzanine Level next to Gate C16.
After the Central Security Checkpoint, turn right and proceed to the entrance located just before Gate D1.
Located outside security above Southwest Airlines ticketing counter on the Mezzanine Level.
After the Central Security Checkpoint, turn right and take the shuttle to the North Satellite Terminal. The lounge is located on the mezzanine level above Gates N13-18.
After exiting the train, take the escalator to the Concourse Level and turn left. Bambuza is located on the left hand side.
Mezzanine Level, next to Gate S9.
